- id: xstate-processor
  subject: Replace manual status mutations with XState machine in processor/registry
  status: pending
  description: Install xstate, define ProcessorMachine (idle->running->error|idle->stopped), use createActor per processor. Registry stores actors. Processor status reads from actor.getSnapshot().value.
  effort: medium
  category: refactor
  blocking: [dual-streams]
  blockedBy: []
  acceptance:
    - xstate in package.json dependencies
    - src/machine.ts exports ProcessorMachine (createMachine)
    - src/processor.ts uses createActor(ProcessorMachine) instead of manual status mutations
    - src/registry.ts stores actor per entry, status derived from actor snapshot
    - ProcessorStatus type remains compatible (idle|running|error|stopped)
    - inspect()/snapshot() still work
  edge_cases:
    - xstate v5 API differs from v4 — must witness createMachine/createActor shapes
    - actor.send() is sync, start() is async — actor lifecycle must match

- id: dual-streams
  subject: Add stderr stream to ProcessorHandle for error and signal chunks
  status: pending
  description: ProcessorHandle gains stderr:AsyncIterable<ErrorChunk|SignalChunk>. Transform output is tee-split — error/signal types route to stderr, all others to stdout. stdio.ts writes error/signal to process.stderr, normal chunks to process.stdout.
  effort: medium
  category: feature
  blocking: []
  blockedBy: [xstate-processor]
  acceptance:
    - ProcessorHandle.stderr exists as AsyncIterable<ErrorChunk|SignalChunk>
    - ProcessorHandle.output (stdout) never emits error/signal chunks
    - stdio.ts writes error/signal chunks to process.stderr
    - ErrorChunk and SignalChunk types imported from chunk-aliases
  edge_cases:
    - stderr consumer may not be attached — must buffer or drop safely (use async tee pattern)
    - pipe() composition must propagate stderr from all stages
